radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. A tiny hypodensity in segment VII of the liver likely represents a simple cyst or biliary hamartoma. Normal pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands. Multiple nonobstructing punctate renal stones bilaterally. Retrocecal appendix is dilated and hyperemic measuring up to 1 cm with adjacent fat stranding.
